# PayMongo Environment Configuration Template

# Copy this file to .env.local in both frontend and backend directories
# Then fill in your actual PayMongo API keys

## BACKEND (.env)

# PayMongo API Configuration
PAYMONGO_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_test_your_public_key_here
PAYMONGO_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here
PAYMONGO_API_URL=https://api.paymongo.com/v1

# Frontend URL (for payment redirects)
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173

# Database Configuration
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_USER=root
DB_PASSWORD=your_db_password
DB_NAME=cocolytics

# Server Configuration
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=development

# JWT Secret
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key_here_change_in_production

# Mail Configuration (optional - for payment receipts)
MAIL_SERVICE=gmail
MAIL_USER=your_email@gmail.com
MAIL_PASS=your_app_password

## FRONTEND (.env)

# PayMongo Public Key (safe to expose)
VITE_PAYMONGO_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_test_your_public_key_here

# API Base URL
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Environment
VITE_ENV=development

## Environment Variables Explanation

### PAYMONGO_PUBLIC_KEY
- Public API key from PayMongo dashboard
- Used for client-side payment initialization
- Starts with 'pk_'
- Can be shared safely

### PAYMONGO_SECRET_KEY
- Secret API key from PayMongo dashboard
- Used for server-side API calls
- Starts with 'sk_'
- ⚠️ KEEP SECRET - NEVER expose in frontend

### PAYMONGO_API_URL
- PayMongo API endpoint
- Production: https://api.paymongo.com/v1
- Do not change unless instructed by PayMongo

### FRONTEND_URL
- Your frontend application URL
- Used for payment redirects and callbacks
- Make sure CORS is configured

## Getting PayMongo Keys

1. Create account at https://paymongo.com
2. Complete KYC verification
3. Log in to PayMongo Dashboard
4. Navigate to: Developers → API Keys
5. Copy Public Key (pk_...)
6. Copy Secret Key (sk_...)
7. Paste into .env files

## Security Tips

✅ DO:
- Store secret keys in .env files
- Add .env to .gitignore
- Use different keys for test and production
- Rotate keys periodically
- Use HTTPS in production

❌ DON'T:
- Commit .env files to git
- Share secret keys
- Use test keys in production
- Log secret keys
- Hardcode keys in source code

## Production Checklist

□ Update PAYMONGO_SECRET_KEY to production key
□ Update FRONTEND_URL to production domain
□ Change NODE_ENV to 'production'
□ Update JWT_SECRET to a strong value
□ Enable HTTPS
□ Configure CORS properly
□ Set up webhook signature verification
□ Test full payment flow
□ Monitor payment transactions
□ Set up error logging

## Development Tips

- Use PayMongo test keys for development
- Test all payment methods before deployment
- Use ngrok to test webhooks locally:
  ```
  ngrok http 3000
  # Then set webhook URL in PayMongo to: https://yourngrokurl.ngrok.io/api/payments/webhook
  ```

